  string
  line 2
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `19. Power to arrest.`
  line `20. Retention of property.`
  line `21. Retention of records.`
  line `22. Presumption as to records or property in certain cases.`
  line `23. Presumption in inter - connected transactions.`
  line `24. Burden of proof.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPELLATE T RIBUNAL`
  line `25. Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `26. Appeal to Appellate Tribu nal.`
  line `27. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `28. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `29. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `30. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `31. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `32. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `33. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `34. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `35. Procedure and powers of Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `36. Distribution of business amongst Benches.`
  line `37. Power of Chairperson to transfer cases.`
  line `38. Decision to be by majority.`
  line `39. Right of appellant to take assistance of authorised representative and of Government to appoint`
  line `presenting officers.`
  line `40. Members, etc., to be public servants.`
  line `41. Civil court not to have jurisdiction.`
  line `42. Appeal to High Court.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `S PECIAL C OURTS`
  line `43. Special Courts.`
  line `44. Offences triable by Special Courts.`
  line `45. Offences to be cognizable and non - bailable.`
  line `46. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Special Court.`
  line `47. Appeal and revision.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `A UTHORITIES`
  line `48. Authorities under Act.`
  line `49. Appointment and powers of authorities and other officers.`
  line `50. Powers of authorities regarding summons, production of documents and to give evidence, etc.`
  line `51. Jurisdiction of authorities.`
  line `52. Power o f Central Government to issue directions, etc.`
