  string
  line 3
  line `S ECTIONS.`
  line `53. Empowerment of certain offic ers.`
  line `54. Certain officers to assist in inquiry etc.`
  line `CHAPTER IX`
  line `R ECIPROCAL A RRANGEMENT FOR A SSISTANCE IN C ERTAIN M ATTERS AND P ROCEDURE FOR`
  line `A TTACHMENT AND C ONFISCATION OF P ROPERTY`
  line `55. Definitions.`
  line `56. Agreements with foreign countries.`
  line `57. Letter of request to a contracting State in certain cases.`
  line `58. Assistance to a contracting State in certain cases.`
  line `58A. Special Court to release the property.`
  line `58B. Letter of request of a contracting State or authority for confiscation or release the property.`
  line `59. Reciprocal arrangements for processes and assistance for transfer of accused persons.`
  line `60. Attachment, seizure and confiscation, etc., of property in a contracting State or India.`
  line `61. Procedure in respect of letter of request.`
  line `CHAPTER X`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `62. Punishment for vexatious search.`
  line `63. Punishment for false information or failure to give information, etc.`
  line `64. Cognizance of offences.`
  line `65. Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to apply.`
  line `66. Disclosure of information.`
  line `67. Bar of suits in civil courts.`
  line `68. Notice, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds.`
  line `69. Recovery o f fine or penalty.`
  line `70. Offences by companies.`
  line `71. Act to have overriding effect.`
  line `72. Continuation of proceeding s in the event of death or insolvency.`
  line `72A. Inter - ministerial Co - ordination Committee.`
  line `73. Power to make rules.`
  line `74. Rules to be laid before Parliament.`
  line `75. Power to remove difficulties.`
  line `THE SCHEDULE.`
