obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE PREVENTION OF MONEY - LAUNDERING ACT, 2002`
  line `A CT N O. 15 OF 2003`
  line `[17 th January, 2003.]`
  line `An Act to prevent money - laundering and to provide for confiscation of property derived from, or`
  line `involved in, money - laundering and for matters connected t herewith or incidental thereto.`
  line `W HEREAS the Political Declaration and Global Programme of Action, annexed to the resolution`
  line `S - 17/2 was adopted by the General Assembly of the United Nations at its seventeenth special session on`
  line `the t wen ty - third day of February, 1990;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the Political Declaration adopted by the Special Session of the United Nations`
  line `General Assembly held on 8th to 10th June, 1998 calls upon the Member States to adopt national`
  line `money - laundering legislation and p ro gramme;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS it is considered necessary to implement the aforesaid resolution and the Declaration.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Fifty - third Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Prevention of Money -`
  line `laundering Act, 2002.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall come into force on such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and dif ferent dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and`
  line `any reference in any such provision to the commenceme nt of this Act shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `the coming into force of that provision.`
  line `2. Definitions. — ( 1 ) In this Act, unless t he context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ Adjudicating Authority ” means an Adjudicating Authority appointed unde r sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 6;`
  line `( b ) “ Appellate Tribunal ” means the Appellate Tribuna l 2 [referred to in] section 25;`
  line `( c ) “ Assistant Director ” means an Assistant Director appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 49;`
  line `( d ) “ attachment ” means prohibition of transfer, conversion, disposition or movement of property`
  line `by an order issued under Chapter III;`
  line `3 [( da ) “ authorised person ” me ans an authorised person as defined in clause ( c ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999);]`
  line `( e ) “ banking company ” means a banking company or a co - operative bank to which the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) applies and includes any bank or banking institution referre d to in`
  line `section 51 of that Act;`
  line `( f ) “ Bench ” means a B ench of the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `4 [( fa) ” b eneficial owner ” means an individual who ultimately owns or controls a client of a`
  line `reporting entity or the person on whose behalf a transaction is being conducted and includes a person`
  line `who exercises ultimate effective control over a juridical person;]`
  line `( g ) “ Chairperson ” means the Chairpe rson of the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( h ) “ chit fund company ” means a company managing, conducting or supervising, as foreman,`
  line `agent or in any other capacity, chits as defined in section 2 of the Chit Funds Act, 1982 (40 of 1982);`
  line `1. 1st July, 2005, vide notification No. G. S. R. 436( E ), dated 1st July, 2005, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, s ec. 3( i ).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 232, for “established under” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
