  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `1 [ ( ra ) “ offence of cross border implications ”, means —`
  line `( i ) any conduct by a person at a place outside India which constitutes an offence at that place`
  line `and which would have constituted an offence specified in Part A, Part B or Part C of the`
  line `Schedule, had it been committed in India and if such person 2 [ transfers i n any manner] the`
  line `proceeds of such conduct or part thereof to India; or`
  line `( ii ) any offence specified in Part A, Part B or Part C of the Schedule which has been`
  line `committed in India and the proceeds of crime, or part thereof have been transferred to a place`
  line `out side India or any attempt has been made to transfer the proceeds of crime, or part thereof from`
  line `India to a place outside India.`
  line `Explanation. — Nothing contained in this clause shall adversely affect any investigation,`
  line `enquiry, trial or proceeding before any authority in respect of the offences specified in Part A or`
  line `Part B of the Schedule to the Act before the commencement of the Prevention of Money -`
  line `launder ing (Amendment) Act, 2009 (21 of 2009);`
  line `( rb ) “ payment system ” means a system that enables payment to be effected between a payer and a`
  line `beneficiary, involving clearing, payment or settlement service or all of them.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “ payment system ” includes the systems`
  line `enabling credit card operations, debit card operations, smart card operations, money transfer`
  line `operations or similar operations;`
  line `( rc ) “ payment system operator ” means a person who operates a payment system and such person`
  line `includes his overseas principal.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this claus e, “ overseas principal ” means, —`
  line `( A ) in the case of a person, being an individual, such individual residing outside India, who`
  line `owns or controls or manages, directly or indirectly, the activities or functions of payment system`
  line `in India;`
  line `( B ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, Karta of such Hindu undivided family residing`
  line `outside India who owns or controls or manages, directly or indirectly, the activities or functions`
  line `of payment system in India;`
  line `( C ) in the case of a company, a firm, an association of persons, a body of indivi duals, an`
  line `artificial juridical person, whether incorporated or not, such company, firm, association of`
  line `persons, body of individuals, artificial juridical person incorporated or registered outside India or`
  line `existing as such and which owns or controls or mana ges, directly or indirectly, the activities or`
  line `function s of payment system in India;]`
  line `( s ) “ person ” includes —`
  line `( i ) an individual,`
  line `( ii ) a Hindu undivided family,`
  line `( iii ) a company,`
  line `( iv ) a firm,`
  line `( v ) an association of persons or a body of individual s, whether inc orporated or not,`
  line `( vi ) every artificial juridical person not falling within any of the preceding sub - clauses, and`
  line `( vii ) any agency, office or branch owned or controlled by any of the above persons mentione d`
  line `in the preceding sub - clauses;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 2, for “remits” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
