  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `1 [ ( sa ) “ person carrying on designated business or profession ” means, —`
  line `( i ) a person carrying on activities for playing games of chance for cash or kind, and includes`
  line `such activities associated with casino;`
  line `2 [ ( ii ) Inspector - General of Registration appointed under section 3 of the Registration`
  line `Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) as may be notified by the Central Government; ]`
  line `( iii ) real estate agent, as may be notified by the Central Government;`
  line `( iv ) dealer in pr ecious metals, precious stones and other high value goods, as may be notified`
  line `by the Central Government;`
  line `( v ) person engaged in safekeeping and administration of cash and liquid securities on behalf`
  line `of other persons, as may be notified by the Central Govern ment; or`
  line `( vi ) person carrying on such other activities as the Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `so designate, from time to time;`
  line `(sb) “ precious metal ” means gold, silver, platinum, palladium or rhodium or such other metal as`
  line `may be notified by the C entral Government;`
  line `(sc) ” precious stone ” means diamond, emerald, ruby, sapphire or any such other stone as may be`
  line `notif ied by the Central Government;]`
  line `( t ) “ prescribed ” means prescribe d by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( u ) “ proceeds of crime ” means any property derived or obtained, directly or indirectly, by any`
  line `person as a result of criminal activity relating to a scheduled offence or the value of any such pro perty`
  line `3 [or where such property is taken or held outside the country, then the proper ty equivalent in value`
  line `held within the country] 4 [or abroad];`
  line `5 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that “ proceeds of crime ” include`
  line `property not only derived or obtained from the scheduled offence but also any property which may`
  line `directly or indirectly be derived or obtained as a result of any criminal activity relatable to the`
  line `scheduled offence;]`
  line `( v ) “ property ” means any property or assets of every description, whether corporeal or`
  line `incorporeal, movable or immovable, tangible or intangible and includes deeds and instruments`
  line `evidencing title to, or interest in, such property or assets, whereve r located;`
  line `1 [ Explanat ion. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the term “ property ” includes`
  line `property of any kind used in the commission of an offence under this Act or any of the scheduled`
  line offences;
  line `( va ) “ real estate agent ” means a real estate agent as define d in clause ( 88 ) of section 65 of`
  line `the Finance Act, 1994 ( 3 2 of 1994 );]`
  line `( w ) “ records ” include the records maintained in the form of books or stored in a computer or such`
  line `o ther form as may be prescribed;`
  line `1 [( wa ) “ reporting entity ” means a banking company, financial institution, intermediary or a`
  line `person carrying on a designated business or profession;]`
  line `( x ) “ Schedule ” means the Schedule to this Act;`
  line `( y ) “ scheduled offence ” means —`
  line `( i ) the offences specified under Par t A of the Schedule; or`
  line `6 [( ii ) the offences specified under Part B of the Schedule if the total value involved in such`
  line `offences is 7 [one crore rupees ] or more; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 192, for sub - clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 145 (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 192 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 2, for sub - clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 20 of 20 15, s. 145, for “thirty lakh rupees” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `( iii ) the offences specified under Part C of the Schedule.]`
  line `( z ) “ Special Court ” means a Court of Session designated as Special Court under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `s ection 43;`
  line `( za ) “ transfer ” includes sale, purchase, mortgage, pledge, gift, loan or any other form of transfer`
  line `of ri ght, title, possession or lien;`
  line `( zb ) “ value ” means the fair market value of any property on the date of its acquisition by any`
  line `person, or if such date cannot be determined, the date on which such property is possessed by such`
  line person.
  line `( 2 ) Any reference, in this Act or the Schedule, to any enactment o r any provision thereof shall, in`
  line `relation to an area in which such enactment or such provision is not in force, be construed as a reference`
  line `to the correspon ding law or the relevant provisi ons of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
  line `CHAPTE R II`
  line `O FFENCE OF M ONEY - L AUNDERING`
  line `3. Offence of money - laundering. — Whosoever directly or indirectly attempts to indulge or`
  line `knowingly assists or knowingly is a party or is actually involved in any process or activity connected with`
  line `the 1 [proceeds of crime including its concealment, possession, acquisition or use and projecting or`
  line `claiming] it as untainted proper ty shall be guilty of offence of money - laundering.`
  line `2 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that, —`
  line `( i ) a person shall be guilty of offence of money - laundering if such person is found to have`
  line `directly or indirectly attempted to indulge or knowingly assisted or knowingly is a party or is actually`
  line `involved in one or more of the following processes or activities connected with proceeds of crime,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `(a) concealment; or`
  line `( b ) possession; or`
  line `( c ) acquisition; or`
  line `( d ) use; or`
  line `( e ) projecting as untainted property; or`
  line `( f ) claiming as untainted property,`
  line `in any manner whatsoever;`
  line `( ii ) the process or activity connected with proceeds of crime is a continuing activity and continues`
  line `till such time a person is directly or indirectly enjoying the proceeds of crime by its concealment or`
  line `possession or acquisition or use or projecting it as untainted property or claiming it as u ntainted`
  line `property in any manner whatsoever.]`
  line `4. Punishm ent for money - laundering. — Whoever commits the offence of money - laundering shall`
  line `be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which`
  line `may extend to seve n years and shall also be liable to fine 3 ***:`
  line `Provided that where the proceeds of crime involved in money - laundering relates to any offence`
  line `specified under paragraph 2 of Part A of the Schedule, the provisions of this section shall have effect as if`
  line `for the words “ whic h may extend to seven years ”, th e words “ which may extend to ten years ” had been`
  line substituted.
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `A TTACHMENT, A DJUDICATION AND C ONFISCATION`
  line `5. Attachment of propert y involved in money - laundering. — 4 [ ( 1 )Where the Director or any other`
  line `officer not below the rank of Deputy Director authorised by the Director for the purposes of this`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 o f 2013, s. 3, for “proceeds of crime and projecting” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 193 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. The words “which may extend to five lakh rupees” omitted by Act 2 o f 2013, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `section, has reason to believe (the reason for such belief to be recorded in writing), on the basis of`
  line `material in his possession, that —`
  line `( a ) any person is in possession of any proceeds of crime; and`
  line `( b ) such proceeds of crime are likely to be concealed, transferred or dealt with in any manner`
  line `which may result in frustrating any proceedings relating to confiscation of such proceeds of crime`
  line `under this Chapter,`
  line `he may, by order in writing, provisionally att ach such property for a period not exceeding one hundred`
  line `and eighty days from the date of the order, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that no such order of attachment shall be made unless, in relation to the scheduled offence, a`
  line `report has bee n forwarded to a Magistrate under section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), or a complaint has been filed by a person authorised to investigate the offence mentioned in`
  line `that Schedule, before a Magistrate or court for taking cognizance of the scheduled offence, as the case`
  line `may be, or a similar report or complaint has been made or filed under the corresponding law of any other`
  line `countr y:`
  line `Provided further that, notwithstanding anything contained in 1 [first proviso], any property of any`
  line `person may be attached under this section if the Director or any other officer not below the rank of`
  line `Deputy Director authorised by him for the purposes of this section has reason to believe (the reasons for`
  line `such belief to be recorded in writing), on the basis of material in his possession, that if such property`
  line `involved in money - laundering is not attached immediately under this Chapter, the non - attachment o f the`
  line `property is likely to frustrate any proceeding under this Act: ]`
  line `2 [Provided also that for the purposes of computing the period of one hundred and eighty days, the`
  line `period during which the proceedings under this section is stayed by the High Court, shal l be excluded and`
  line `a further period not exceeding thirty days from the date of order of vacation of such stay order shall be`
  line counted.];
  line `( 2 ) The Director, or any other officer not below the rank of Deputy Director, shall, immediately after`
  line `attachment under s ub - section ( 1 ), forward a copy of the order, along with the material in his possession,`
  line `referred to in that sub - section, to the Adjudicating Authority, in a sealed envelope, in the manner as may`
  line `be prescribed and such Adjudicating Authority shall keep such order and material for su ch period as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Every order of attachment made under sub - section ( 1 ) shall cease to have effect after the expiry of`
  line `the period specified in that sub - section or on the date of an order made under 3 [sub - section ( 3 )] of`
  line `s ection 8, whichever is earlier.`
  line `( 4 ) Nothing in this section shall prevent the person interested in the enjoyment of the immovable`
  line `property attached under sub - s ection ( 1 ) from such enjoyment.`
  line `Explana tion. — For the purposes of this sub - sec tion, “ person interested ”, in relation to any immovable`
  line `property, includes all persons claiming or entitled to clai m any interest in the property.`
  line `( 5 ) The Director or any other officer who provisionally attaches any property under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `shall, within a period of thirty days from such attachment, file a complaint stating the facts of such`
  line `attachment before the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `6. Adjudicating Authori ties, composition, powers, etc. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall, by`
  line `notification, appoint 4 [an Adjudicating Authority] to exercise jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred`
  line `by or under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) An Adjudicating Authority shall consist of a Cha irperson and two other Members:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 146, for “clause ( b )” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 208, ibid., for “ sub - section ( 2 ) ” (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 4, for “one or more Adjudicating Authorities” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `Provided that one Member each shall be a person having experien ce in the field of law,`
  line `administ ration, finance or accountancy.`
  line `( 3 ) A person shall, however, not be qualified for appointment as Member of an Adjudicating`
  line `Authority, —`
  line `( a ) in the field of law, unless he —`
  line `( i ) is qualified for ap pointment as District Judge; or`
  line `( ii ) has been a member of the Indian Legal Service and has held a p ost in Grade I of that`
  line service;
  line `( b ) in the field of finance, accountancy or administration unless he possesses such qualifications,`
  line `as may be p rescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) The Central Government shall appoint a Member to be the Chairperson of the Adjudicating`
  line Authority.
  line `( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of this Act, —`
  line `( a ) the jurisdiction of the Adjudicating Authority may b e exercised by Benches thereof;`
  line `( b ) a Bench may be constituted by the Chairperson of the Adjudicating Authority with one or two`
  line `Members as the Chairperson of the Adjud icating Authority may deem fit;`
  line `( c ) the Benches of the Adjudicating Authority shall ordinarily sit at New Delhi and at such other`
  line `places as the Central Government may, in con sultation with the Chairperson, by notification, specify;`
  line `( d ) the Central Government shall, by notification, specify the areas in relation to which each`
  line `Bench of the Adjudicating Authority may exercise jurisdictio n.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained i n sub - section ( 5 ), the Chairperson may transfer a Member`
  line `f rom one Bench to another Bench.`
  line `( 7 ) If at any stage of the hearing of any case or matter it appears to the Chairperson or a Member that`
  line `the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be hea rd by a Bench consisting of two Members, the`
  line `case or matt er may be transferred by the Chairperson or, as the case may be, referred to him for transfer,`
  line `to such Bench a s the Chairperson may deem fit.`
  line `( 8 ) The Chairperson and every Member shall hold office as such for a term of five years from the date`
  line `on w hich he enters upon his office:`
  line `Provided that no Chairperson or other Member shall hold office as such after he has attai ned the age`
  line `of 1 [ sixty - five] years.`
  line `( 9 ) The salary and allowances payable to and the other terms and conditions of service of the Member`
  line `shall be s uch as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Member shall be varied to his disadvantage after appointment.`
  line `( 10 ) If, for reasons other than temporary absence, any vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairperson`
  line `or any other Member, then, the Central Government shall appoint another person in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act to fill the vacancy and the proce edings may be continued before the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
  line `( 11 ) The Chairperson or any other Member may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Central Governm ent, resign his office:`
  line `Provided that the Chairperson or any other Member shall, unless he is permitted by the Central`
  line `Government to relinquish his office sooner, continue to hold office until the expiry of three months from the`
  line `date of receipt of such notice or until a person d uly appointed as his successor enters upon his office or until`
  line `the expiry of his term of off ice, whichever is the earliest.`
  line `( 12 ) The Chairperson or any other Member shall not be removed from his office except by an order made`
  line `by the Central Government after giving ne cessary opportunity of hearing.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 4, for “sixty - two” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `( 13 ) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, the senior - most Member shall act as the Chairperson of the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `until t he date on which a new Chairpers on, appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such`
  line `v acancy, enters upon his office.`
  line `( 14 ) When the Chairperson of the Adjudicating Authority is unable to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `absence, illness or any other cause, the senior - most Member shall discharge the functions of the Chairperson of`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority until the date on which the Chairperson of the Adjudicatin g Authority resumes his`
  line duties.
  line `( 15 ) The Adjudicating Authority shall not b e bound by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other`
  line `provisions o f this Act, the Adjudicating Authority shall have powers to regulate its own procedure.`
  line `7. Sta ff of Adjudicating Authorities. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall provide each Adjudicating`
  line `Authority with such officers and employees as that Government may think fit.`
  line `( 2 ) The officers and employees of the Adjudicating Authority shall dis charge their functions under the`
  line `general superintendence of the Chairperson of the Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `( 3 ) The salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and employees of the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall be such as may be p rescribed.`
  line `8. Adjudication. — ( 1 ) On receipt of a complaint under sub - section ( 5 ) of section 5, or applications made`
  line `under sub - section ( 4 ) of section 17 or under sub - section ( 10 ) of section 18, if the Adjudicating Authority has`
  line `reason to believe that any person has c ommitted an 1 [ offence under section 3 or is in possession of proceeds of`
  line `crime], it may serve a notice of not less than thirty days on such person calling upon him to indicate the`
  line `sources of his income, earning or assets, out of which or by means of which he has acquired the property`
  line `attached unde r sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5, or, seized 2 [or frozen] under section 17 or section 18, the evidence`
  line `on which he relies and other relevant information and particulars, and to show cause why all or any of such`
  line `properties should not be d eclared to be the properties inv olved in money - laundering and confiscated by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line `Provided that where a notice under this sub - section specifies any property as being held by a person on`
  line `behalf of any other person, a copy of such notice shall also be served upon such other person:`
  line `Provided further that where such property is held jointl y by more than one person, such notice shall be`
  line `served to all persons holding such property.`
  line `( 2 ) The Adjud icating Authority shall, after —`
  line `( a ) considering the reply, if any, to the notic e issued under sub - section ( 1 );`
  line `( b ) hearing the aggrieved person and th e Director or any other officer author ised by him in this behalf;`
  line and
  line `( c ) taking into account all relevant materia ls placed on record before him,`
  line `by an order, record a finding whether all or any of the properties referred to in the notice issued under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) ar e involved in money - laundering:`
  line `Provided that if the property is claimed by a person, other than a person to whom the notice had been`
  line `issued, such person shall also be given an opportunity of being heard to prove that the property is no t involved`
  line `in money - laundering.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the Adjudicating Authority decides under sub - section ( 2 ) that any property is involved in`
  line `money - laundering, he shall, by an order in writing, confirm the attachment of the property made under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5 or retention of propert y or 3 [record seized or frozen under section 17 or section 18`
  line `and record a finding to that effect, whereupon such attachment or retention or freezing of the seized or frozen`
  line `property] or record s hall —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 5, for “offence under section 3” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 6 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( a ) continue during 1 [investigation for a period not exceeding 2 [three hundred and sixty - five days]`
  line `or] the pendency of the proceedings relating to any 3 [offence under this Act before a court or under`
  line `the corresponding law of any other country, before the competent court of criminal jurisdiction`
  line `outside India, as the case may be; and]`
  line `4 [( b ) become final after an order of confiscation is passed under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 7 )`
  line `of section 8 or section 58B or sub - section (2A) of section 60 by the 5 [Special Court];]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of computing the period of three hundred and sixty - five days`
  line `under clause ( a ), the period during which the investigation is stayed by any court under any law for`
  line `the time being in force shall be excluded.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where the provisional order of attachment made under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5 has been`
  line `confirmed under sub - section ( 3 ), the Director or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf shall`
  line `forthwith take the 7 [possession of the property attached under section 5 or frozen under sub - section ( 1A )`
  line `of section 17, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that if it is not practicable to ta ke possession of a property frozen under sub - section ( 1 A ) of`
  line `section 17, the order of confiscation shall have the same effect as if the property had been taken`
  line `possession of.]`
  line `8 [( 5 ) Where on conclusion of a trial of an offence under this Act, the Special Court finds that the`
  line `offence of money - laundering has been committed, it shall order that such property involved in the money -`
  line `laundering or which has been used for commission of the offence of money - laundering shall stand`
  line `confiscated to the Central Governme nt.`
  line `( 6 ) Where on conclusion of a trial under this Act, the Special Court finds that the offence of money -`
  line `laundering has not taken place or the property is not involved in money - laundering, it shall order release`
  line `of such property to the person entitled to r eceive it.`
  line `( 7 ) Where the trial under this Act cannot be conducted by reason of the death of the accused or the`
  line `accused being declared a proclaimed offender or for any other reason or having commenced but could not`
  line `be concluded, the Special Court shall, on an application moved by the Director or a person claiming to be`
  line `entitled to possession of a property in respect of which an order has been passed under sub - section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 8, pass appropriate orders regarding confiscation or release of the property, as the case may be,`
  line `involved in the offence of money - laundering after having reg ard to the material before it.]`
  line `9 [ ( 8 ) Where a property stands confiscated to the Central Government under sub - section ( 5 ), the`
  line `Special Court, in such manner as may be prescribed, may also direct the Central Government to restore`
  line `such confiscated property or part thereof of a claimant with a legitimate interest in the property, who may`
  line `have suffered a quantifiable loss as a result of the offence of money laundering:`
  line `Prov ided that the Special Court shall not consider such claim unless it is satisfied that the claimant`
  line `has acted in good faith and has suffered the loss despite having taken all reasonable precautions and is not`
  line `involved in the offence of money - laundering: ]`
  line `1 [ Provided further that the Special Court may, if it thinks fit, consider the claim of the claimant for the`
  line `purposes of restoration of such properties during the trial of the case in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed. ]`
  line `9. Vesting of property in Central Government. — Where an order of confiscation has been made`
  line `under 10 [sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 7 ) of section 8 or section 58B or sub - section ( 2A ) of section 60] in`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 22, for “ninety days” (w.e.f. 20 - 3 - 2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 6, for “scheduled offence before a court; and” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 147, fo r “Adjudicating Authority” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 22 (w.e.f. 20 - 3 - 2019).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 6, for “possession of the attached property” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub - sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 147 (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 7, for “sub - section ( 6 ) of section 8” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `respect of any property of a person, all the rights and title in such property shall vest absolutely in the`
  line `Central Government free from all encumbrances:`
  line `Provided that where the 1 [Special Court or the Adjudicating Authority, as the case may be,] after`
  line `giving an opportunity of being heard to any other person interested in the property attached under this`
  line `Chapter, or seized 2 [or frozen] under Chapter V, is of the opinion that any en cumbrance on the property or`
  line `lea se - hold interest has been created with a view to defeat the provisions of this Chapter, it may, by order,`
  line `declare such encumbrance or lease - hold interest to be void and thereupon the aforesaid property shall vest`
  line `in the Central Government free from such e ncum brances or lease - hold interest:`
  line `Provid ed further that nothing in this section shall operate to discharge any person from any liability in`
  line `respect of such encumbrances which may be enforced against such person by a suit for damages.`
  line `10. Management of properties confiscated under this Chapter. — ( 1 ) The Central Government`
  line `may, by order published in the Official Gazette, appoint as many of its officers (not below the rank of a`
  line `Joint Secretary to the Government of India) as it thinks fit to perform the functions of an Administrator.`
  line `( 2 ) The Administr ator appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) shall receive and manage the property in`
  line `relation to which an order has been made under 3 [sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 6) or sub - section ( 7 ) of`
  line `section 8 or section 58B or sub - section (2A) of section 60] in such manner and subject to such c onditions`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) The Administrator shall also take such measures, as the Central Government may direct, to`
  line `dispose of the property which is vested in the Central Government under section 9.`
  line `11. Power regarding summons, production of documents and evidence, etc. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Adjudicating Authority shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedu re, 1908 (5 of 1908) while tryin g a suit in respect of the fo llowing`
  line `matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a banking company or a`
  line `financial institution or a comp any, and examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compel ling the production of records;`
  line `( d ) re ceiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses and documents; and`
  line `( f ) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line `( 2 ) All the persons so summoned shall be bound to attend in person or through authorised agents, as`
  line `the Adjudicating Authority may direct, and shall be bound to state the truth upon any subject respecting`
  line `which they are exa mined or make statements, and produce suc h documents as may be required.`
  line `( 3 ) Every proceeding under this secti on shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `O BLIGATIONS OF BANKING COMPANIES, FINANCIAL INSTITUTIONS AND INTERMEDIARIES`
  line `4 [ 11A. Verification of Identity by Reporting Entity. — ( 1 ) Every Reporting Entity shall verify the`
  line `identity of its clients and the beneficial owner, by —`
  line `( a ) authentication under the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits`
  line `and Services ) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016) if the reporting entity is a banking company; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 7, for “Adjudicating Authority” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by s.7, ib id. (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for “sub - section ( 6 ) of section 8” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 14 of 2019, s. 2 7 (w.e.f. 25 - 07 - 2019).`
