  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `( b ) offline verification under the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies,`
  line `Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016); or`
  line `( c ) use of passport issued under section 4 of the Passports Act, 1967 (15 of 1967); or`
  line `( d ) use of any other officially valid document or modes of identification as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if satisfied that a repor ting entity other than banking`
  line `company, complies with such the standards of privacy and security under the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of`
  line `Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016), and it is necessary and`
  line `expedient to do so, by notification, permit such entity to perform authentication under clause ( a ):`
  line `Provided further that no notification under the first proviso shall be issued without consultation with the`
  line `Unique Identification Authority of India established under sub - s ection ( 1 ) of section 11 of the Aadhaar`
  line `(Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016) and the`
  line `appropriate regulator.`
  line `( 2 ) If any reporting entity performs authentication under clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ), to verify the identity of`
  line `its client or the beneficial owner it shall make the other modes of identification under clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( d )`
  line `of sub - section ( 1 ) also available to such client or the beneficial owner.`
  line `( 3 ) The use of modes of identification under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be a voluntary choice of every client`
  line `or beneficial owner who is sought to be identified and no client or beneficial owner shall be denied`
  line `services for not having an Aadhaar number.`
  line `( 4 ) If, for identification of a client or beneficial owner, authentication or offline verification under`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 1 ) is used, neither his core biometric information nor his Aadhaar`
  line `number shall be stored.`
  line `( 5 ) Nothing in this section shall prevent the Central Government from notifying additional safeguards`
  line `on any reporting entity in respect of verification of the identity of its client or beneficial owner.`
  line `Explanation. — The expressions “ Aadhaar number ” and “ core biometric information ” shall have the`
  line `same meanings as are respectively assigned to them in clauses ( a ) and ( j ) of section 2 of the Aadhaar`
  line `(Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016). ]`
  line `1 [ 12. Reporting entity to maintain re cords. — ( 1 ) Every reporting entity shall —`
  line `( a ) maintain a record of all transactions, including information relating to transactions covered`
  line `under clause ( b ), in such manner as to enable it to reconstruct individual transactions;`
  line `( b ) furnish to the Director within such time as may be prescribed, information relating to such`
  line `transactions, whether attempted or executed, the nature and value of which may be prescribed;`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( e ) maintain record of documents evidencing identity of its clients and benef icial owners as well`
  line `as account files and business correspondence relating to its clients.`
  line `( 2 ) Every information maintained, furnished or verified, save as otherwise provided under any law`
  line `for the time being in force, shall be kept confidential.`
  line `( 3 ) The re cords referred to in clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall be maintained for a period of five`
  line `years from the date of transaction between a client and the reporting entity.`
  line `( 4 ) The records referred to in clause ( e ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall be maintained for a period of five`
  line `years after the business relationship between a client and the reporting entity has ended or the account has`
  line `been closed, whichever is later.`
  line `( 5 ) The Central Government may, by notification, exempt any reporting entity or class of reporting`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 9, for section 12 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Clause s ( c ) and ( d ) omitted by Act 14 of 2019, s. 2 8 (w.e.f. 25 - 07 - 2019).`
