  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `entities from any obligation under this Chapter.]`
  line `1 [ 12A. Access to information. — ( 1 ) The Director may call for from any reporting entity any of the`
  line `recor ds referred to in 2 [section 11A, sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12, sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12AA ] and`
  line `any additional information as he considers necessary for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Every reporting entity shall furnish to the Director such information as may be requ ired by him`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ) within such time and in such manner as he may specify.`
  line `( 3 ) Save as otherwise provided under any law for the time being in force, every information sought`
  line `by the Director u nder sub - section ( 1 ), shall be kept confidential.]`
  line `3 [ 12AA. Enhanced due diligence. — ( 1 ) Every reporting entity shall, prior to the commencement of`
  line `each specified transaction, —`
  line `( a ) verify the identity of the clients undertaking such specified transaction by authentication`
  line `under the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services)`
  line `Act, 2016 (18 of 2016) in such manner and subject to such conditions, as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that where verification requires authentication of a person who is not entitled to obtain`
  line `an Aadhaar number under t he provisions of the said Act, verification to authenticate the identity of`
  line `the client undertaking such specified transaction shall be carried out by such other process or mode,`
  line `as may be prescribed;`
  line `( b ) take additional steps to examine the ownership and f inancial position, including sources of`
  line `funds of the client, in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line `( c ) take additional steps as may be prescribed to record the purpose behind conducting the`
  line `specified transaction and the intended nature of the relationship b etween the transaction parties.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the client fails to fulfill the conditions laid down under sub - section ( 1 ), the reporting entity`
  line `shall not allow the specified transaction to be carried out.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any specified transaction or series of specifi ed transactions undertaken by a client is`
  line `considered suspicious or likely to involve proceeds of crime, the reporting entity shall increase the future`
  line `monitoring of the business relationship with the client, including greater scrutiny or transactions in su ch`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) The information obtained while applying the enhanced due diligence measures under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) shall be maintained for a period of five years from the date of transaction between a client`
  line `and the reporting entity.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “ specified transaction ” means —`
  line `( a ) any withdrawal or deposit in cash, exceeding such amount;`
  line `( b ) any transaction in foreign exchange, exceeding such amount;`
  line `( c ) any transaction in any high value imports or remittances;`
  line `( d ) such other transaction or class of transactions, in the interest of revenue or where there is a`
  line `high risk or money - laundering or terrorist financing,`
  line `as may be prescribed.]`
  line `13. Pow ers of Director to impose fine. — ( 1 ) The Director may, either of his own motion or on an`
  line `application made by any authority, officer or person, 4 [make such inquiry or cause such inquiry to be`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 194, for “sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12” (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. s. 195, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 11, for certain words, brackets and figures (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
