  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `made, as he thinks fit to be necessary, with regard to the obligations of the reporting entity, unde r this`
  line Chapter].
  line `1 [ (1A) If at any stage of inquiry or any other proceedings before him, the Director having regard to the`
  line `nature and complexity of the case, is of the opinion that it is necessary to do so, he may direct the`
  line `concerned reporting entity to get its records, as may b e specified, audited by an accountant from amongst`
  line `a panel of accountants, maintained by the Central Government for this purpose.`
  line `(1B) The expenses of, and incidental to, any audit under sub - section ( 1A ) shall be borne by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line `2 [ (2 ) If t he Director, in the course of any inquiry, finds that a reporting entity or its designated director`
  line `on the Board or any of its employees has failed to comply with the obligations under this Chapter, then,`
  line `without prejudice to any other action that may be t aken under any other provisions of this Act, he may —`
  line `( a ) issue a warning in writing; or`
  line `( b ) direct such reporting entity or its designated director on the Board or any of its employees, to`
  line `comply with specific instructions; or`
  line `( c ) direct such reporting ent ity or its designated director on the Board or any of its employees, to`
  line `send reports at such interval as may be prescribed on the measures it is taking; or`
  line `( d ) by an order, impose a monetary penalty on such reporting entity or its designated director on`
  line `th e Board or any of its employees, which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees for each failure.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Director shall forward a copy of the order passed under sub - section ( 2 ) to every banking`
  line `company, financial institution or intermediary or person who is a party to the proceedings under that`
  line `sub - section.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the purpose of this section, “ accountant ” shall mean a chartered accountant`
  line `within the meaning of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949).]`
  line `4 [ 14. No civil or criminal proceedings against reporting entity, its directors and employees in`
  line `certain cases. — Save as otherwise provided in section 13, the reporting entity, its directors and`
  line `employees shall not be liable to any civil or criminal proceedings against them for furnishing information`
  line `under clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12.]`
  line `5 [ 15. Procedure and manner of furnishing information by reporting entities. — The Central`
  line `Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank of India, prescribe the procedure and the manner`
  line `of maintaining and furn ishing information by a repor ting entity under 6 [section 11A, sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 12 and sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12AA] for the purpose of implement ing the provisions of this`
  line Act.]
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `S UMMONS, SEARCHES AND SEIZURES, ETC.`
  line `16. Power of survey. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act,`
  line `where an authority, on the basis of m aterial in his possession, has reason to believe (the reasons for such`
  line `belief to be recorded in writing) that an offence under section 3 has been com mitted, he may enter any`
  line `place —`
  line `( i ) within the limits of the area assigned to him; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 11, (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. I ns. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 11 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 14 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 196, for “sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12” (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `( ii ) in respect of which he is authorised for the purposes of this section by such other authority,`
  line `who is assigned the area withi n which such place is situated,`
  line `at which any act constituting the commission of such offence is carried on, and may require any`
  line `p roprietor, employee or any other person who may at that time and place be attending in any manner to,`
  line `or helping in, such act s o as to, —`
  line `( i ) afford him the necessary facility to inspect such records as he may require and which may be`
  line `available at such plac e;`
  line `( ii ) afford him the necessary facility to check or verify the proceeds of crime or any transaction`
  line `related to proceeds of crime which may be found therein; and`
  line `( iii ) furnish such information as he may require as to any matter which may be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any proceedings under this Act.`
  line `Explanation — For the purposes of this sub - section, a place, where an act which constitutes the`
  line `commission of the offence is carried on, shall also include any other place, whether any activity is carried`
  line `on ther ein or not, in which the person carrying on s uch activity states that any of his records or any part of`
  line `his property relating to such act are or is kept.`
  line `( 2 ) The authority referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) shall, after entering any place referred to in that`
  line `sub - section immediately after completion of survey, forward a copy of the reasons so recorded along with`
  line `material in his possession, referred to in that s ub - section, to the Adjudicating Authority in a sealed`
  line `envelope, in the manner as may be prescribed and such Adjudicating Authority shall keep such reasons`
  line `and material for su ch period as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) An authority acting un der this section may —`
  line `( i ) place marks of identification on the records inspected by him and make or cause to be mad e`
  line `extracts or copies there from,`
  line `( ii ) make an inventory of any property checked or verified by him, and`
  line `( iii ) record the statement of any person present in the place which may be useful for, or relevant`
  line `to, any proceeding under this Act.`
  line `17. Search and seizure. — ( 1 ) W here 1 [ the Director or any other officer not below the rank of Deputy`
  line `Director authorised by him for the purposes of this section, ] on the basis of information in his possession,`
  line `has reason to believe (the reason for such belief to be recorded in writing) that any person —`
  line `( i ) has committed any act which c onstitutes money - laundering, or`
  line `( ii ) is in possession of any proceeds of crime i nvolved in money - laundering, or`
  line `( iii ) is in possession of any record s relating to money - laundering, 2 [or]`
  line `2 [( iv ) is in possession of any property related to crime,]`
  line `then, subject to the rules made in this behalf, he may authorise any officer subordinate to him to —`
  line `( a ) enter and search any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft where he has reason to suspect`
  line `tha t such records or proceeds of crime are kept;`
  line `( b ) break open the lock of any door, box, locker, safe, almirah or other receptacle for exercising`
  line `the powers conferred by clause ( a ) where the keys thereof are not available;`
  line `( c ) seize any record or property f o und as a result of such search;`
  line `( d ) place marks of identification on such record or 2 [property, if required or] make or cause to be`
  line `mad e extracts or copies therefrom;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 7, for “the Director” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `( e ) make a note or an inventory of such record or property;`
  line `( f ) examine on oath any person, who is found to be in possession or control of any record or`
  line `property, in respect of all matters relevant for the purposes of an y investigation under this Act:`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [ ( 1 A) Where it is not practicable to seize such record or property, the officer authorised under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), may make an order to freeze such property whereupon the property shall not be`
  line `transferred or otherwise dealt with, except with the prior permission of the officer making such order, and`
  line `a copy of such order shall be served on the person concerned:`
  line `Provided that if, at any time before its confiscation under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 7 ) of`
  line `section 8 or section 58B or sub - section ( 2A ) of section 60, it becomes practical to seize a frozen property,`
  line `the officer authorised under sub - sectio n ( 1 ) may seize such property.]`
  line `( 2 ) The authority, who has been authorised under sub - section (1 ) shall, immediately after search and`
  line `seizure 2 [or upon issuance of a freezing order], forward a copy of the reasons so recorded along with`
  line `material in his possession, referred to in that sub - section, to the Adjudicating Authority i n a sealed`
  line `envelope, in the manner, as may be prescribed and such Adj udicating Authority shall keep such reasons`
  line `and material for such period, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an authority, upon information obtained during survey under section 16, is satisfied that`
  line `any evidence shall be or is likely to be concealed or tamper ed with, he may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, enter and search the building or place where such evidence is located and seize that evidence:`
  line `Provided that no authorisation referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) shall be required for search under this`
  line `su b - section.`
  line `3 [( 4 ) The authority seizing any record or property under sub - section ( 1 ) or freezing any record or`
  line `property under sub - section ( 1A ) shall, within a period of thirty days from such seizure or freezing, as the`
  line `case may be, file an application, requesting for retention of such record or prop erty seized under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) or for continuation of the order of freezing served under sub - section ( 1A ), before the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority.]`
  line `18. Search of persons. — ( 1 ) If an authority, authorised in this behalf by the Central Government by`
  line `general or special order, has reason to believe (the reason for such belief to be recorded in writing) that`
  line `any person has secreted about his person or in a nything under his possession, ownership or control, any`
  line `record or proceeds of crime which may be useful for or relevant to any proceedings under this Act, he`
  line `may search that person and seize such record or property which may be useful for or relevant to any`
  line `proceedings under this Act:`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) The authority, who has been authorised under sub - section ( 1 ) shall, immediately after search and`
  line `seizure, forward a copy of the reasons so recorded along with material in his possession, referred to in that`
  line `sub - section, to the Adjudicating Authority i n a sealed envelope, in the manner, as may be prescribed and`
  line `such Adjudicating Authority shall keep such reasons and material for such period, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an authority is about to search any person, he shall, if such person so requires, ta ke such`
  line `person within twenty - four hours to the nearest Gazetted Officer, superior in rank to him, or a Magistrate:`
  line `Provided that the period of twenty - four hours shall exclude the time necessary for the journey`
  line `undertaken to take such person to the nearest Gazetted Officer, superior in rank to him, or Magistrate’ s`
  line Court.
  line `1. The Proviso omitted by Act 23 of 2019, s. 197 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 3013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub - section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. T he proviso omitted by Act 23 of 2019, s. 198 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `( 4 ) If the requisition under sub - section ( 3 ) is made, the authority shall not detain the person for more`
  line `than twenty - four hours prior to taking him before the Gazetted Officer, superior in rank to him, or the`
  line `Magistrate referred to in that sub - section:`
  line `Provided that the period of twenty - four hours shall exclude the time necessary for the journey from`
  line `the place of detention to the office of the Gazetted Officer, superior in rank to him, or th e Magistrate’ s`
  line Court.
  line `( 5 ) The Gazetted Officer or the Magistrate before whom any such person is brought shall, if he sees`
  line `no reasonable ground for search, forthwith discharge such person but otherwise sh all direct that search be`
  line made.
  line `( 6 ) Before making the search under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 5 ), the authority shall call upon`
  line `two or more persons to attend and witness the search, and the search shall be made i n the presence of such`
  line persons.
  line `( 7 ) The authority shall prepare a list of record or property seized in the course of the search and obtain`
  line `the signatures of the witnesses on the lis t.`
  line `( 8 ) No female shall be searc hed by any one except a female.`
  line `( 9 ) The authority shall record the statement o f the person searched under sub - section ( 1 ) or`
  line `sub - section ( 5 ) in respect of the records or proceeds of crime found or seized in the course of the search:`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 10 ) The authority, seizing any record or property under sub - section ( 1 ) shall, within a period of thirty`
  line `days from such seizure, file an application requesting for retention of such record or property, before the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority.`
  line `19. Power to arrest. — ( 1 ) If the Director, Deputy Director, Assistant Director or any other officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Central Government by general or special order, has on the basis of`
  line `material in his possession, reason to believe (the reas on for such belief to be recorded in writing) that any`
  line `person has been guilty of an offence punishable under this Act, he may arrest such person and shall, as`
  line `soon as may be, inform him of the grounds for such arrest.`
  line `( 2 ) The Director, Deputy Director, Assistant Director or any o ther officer shall, immediately after`
  line `arrest of such person under sub - section ( 1 ), forward a copy of the order along with the material in his`
  line `possession, referred to in that sub - section, to th e Adjudicating Authority in a sealed envelope, in the`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed and such Adjudicating Authority shall keep such order and material for`
  line `suc h period, as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person arrested under sub - section ( 1 ) shall, within twenty - four hours, be taken to a`
  line `2 [Special Court or] Judicial Magistr ate or a Metropolitan Magistrate, as the case may be, having`
  line `jurisdiction:`
  line `Provided that the period of twenty - four hours shall exclude the time necessary for the journey from`
  line `the pl ace of arrest to the 2 [Special Court or] Magistrate’ s Court.`
  line `3 [ 20. Retention of property. — ( 1 ) Where any property has been seized under section 17 or section 18`
  line `or frozen under sub - section ( 1A ) of section 17 and the officer authorised by the Director in this behalf has,`
  line `on the basis of material in his possession, reason to believe (the reason for such belief to be recorded by`
  line `him in writing) that such property is required to be retained for the purposes of adjudication under`
  line `section 8, such property may, if seized, be retained or if frozen, may continue to remain fr ozen, for a`
  line `period not exceeding one hundred and eighty days from the day on which such property was seized or`
  line `frozen, as the case may be.`
  line `(2) The officer authorised by the Director shall, immediately after he has passed an order for retention`
  line `or continuat ion of freezing of the property for purposes of adjudication under section 8, forward a copy of`
  line `the order along with the material in his possession, referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), to the Adjudicating`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 21 of 2009 s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009 ).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s.16, for s ections 20 and 21 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `Authority, in a sealed envelope, in the manner as may b e prescribed and such Adjudicating Authority`
  line `shall keep such order and material for such period as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) On the expiry of the pe riod specified in sub - section ( 1 ), the property shall be returned to the`
  line `person from whom such property was sei zed or whose property was ordered to be frozen unless the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority permits retention or continuation of freezing of such property beyond the said`
  line period.
  line `( 4 ) The Adjudicating Authority, before authorising the retention or continuation of free zing of such`
  line `property beyond the pe riod specified in sub - section ( 1 ), shall satisfy himself that the property is`
  line `prima facie involved in money - laundering and the property is required for the purposes of adjudication`
  line `under section 8.`
  line `( 5 ) Aft er passing the order of confiscation under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 7 ) of section 8,`
  line `1 [ Special Court], shall direct the release of all property other than the property involved in`
  line `money - laundering to the person from whom such property was seized or the persons entitled to receive it.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an order releasing the property has been made by the 2 [ Special Court ] under`
  line `sub - section ( 6) of section 8 or by the Adjudicating Authority under section 58B or sub - section ( 2A ) of`
  line `section 60, t he Director or any officer authorised by him in this behalf may withhold the release of any`
  line `such property for a period of ninety days from the date of 3 [receipt of] such order, if he is of the opinion`
  line `that such property is relevant for the appeal proceedin gs under this Act.`
  line `21. Retention of records. — ( 1 ) Where any records have been seized, under section 17 or section 18`
  line `or frozen under sub - section ( 1A ) of section 17 and the Investigating Officer or any other officer`
  line `authorised by the Director in this behalf has reason to believe that any of such records are required to be`
  line `retained for any inquiry under this Act, such records may if seized, be retained or if frozen, may continue`
  line `to remain frozen, for a period not exceeding one h undred and eighty days from the day on which such`
  line `records were seized or frozen, as the case may be.`
  line `( 2 ) The person, from whom records seized or frozen, shall be entitled to obtain copies of records.`
  line `( 3 ) On the expiry of the period specifie d under sub - sect ion ( 1 ), the records shall be returned to the`
  line `person from whom such records were seized or whose records were ordered to be frozen unless the`
  line `Adjudicating Authority permits retention or continuation of freezing of such records beyond the said`
  line period.
  line `( 4 ) T he Adjudicating Authority, before authorising the retention or continuation of freezing of such`
  line `records beyond the pe riod specified in sub - section ( 1 ), shall satisfy himself that the records are required`
  line `for the purposes of adjudication under section 8.`
  line `( 5 ) After passing of an order of confiscation 4 [ or release under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 6 ) or`
  line `sub - section ( 7 ) of section 8 or section 58B or s ub - section ( 2A ) of section 60 ], the Adjudicating Authority`
  line `shall direct the release of the records to the person from whom such records were seized.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an order releasing the records has been made by the Court 5 [ Adjudicating Authority under`
  line `sub - section ( 5 ) of section 21 ], the Director or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf may`
  line `withhold th e release of any such record for a period of ninety days from the date of 6 [receipt of] such`
  line `order, if he is of the opinion that such record is relevant for the appe al proceedings under this Act.]`
  line `22. Presumption as to record s or property in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where any records or property`
  line `are or is found in the possession or control of any person in the course of a survey or a sea rch 7 [or where`
  line `any record or property is produced by any person or has been resumed or seized from the custody or`
  line `control of any person or has been frozen under this Act or under any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, ] it shall be presumed that —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 148, for “the Court or the Adjudicating Authority, as the case may be” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 148, ibid., for “Court” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 148, ibid. (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 149, for “under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 7 ) of section 8” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 149, ibid., for certain words, brackets, figures and letter s (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 149, ibid. (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s.17 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `( i ) such records or property belong or belongs to suc h person;`
  line `( ii ) the content s of such records are true; and`
  line `( iii ) the signature and every other part of such records which purport to be in the handwriting of`
  line `any particular person or which may reasonably be assumed to have been signed by, or to be in the`
  line `handwriting of, any partic ular person, are in that person’ s handwriting, and in the case of a record,`
  line `stamped, executed or attested, that it was executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to`
  line `have been so stamped, executed or attested.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any records have been received from any place outside India, duly authenticated by such`
  line `authority or person and in such manner as may be prescribed, in the course of proceedings under this Act,`
  line `the Special Court, the Appellate Tribunal or the A djudicating Author ity, as the case may be, shall —`
  line `( a ) presume, that the signature and every other part of such record which purports to be in the`
  line `handwriting of any particular person or which the court may reasonably assume to have been signed`
  line `by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, i s in that person’ s handwriting; and in the`
  line `case of a record executed or attested, that it was executed or attested by the person by whom it`
  line `purports to hav e been so executed or attested;`
  line `( b ) admit the document in evidence, notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such document`
  line `is otherwise admissible in evidence.`
  line `23. Presumption i n inter - connected transactions. — Where money - laundering involves two or more`
  line `inter - connected transactions and one or more such transactions is or are proved to be involved in`
  line `m oney - laundering, then for the p urposes of adjudication or confi scation 1 [under section 8 or for the trial`
  line `of the money - laundering offence, it shall unless otherwise proved to the satisfaction of the Adjudicating`
  line `Authority or the Special Court], be presumed th at the remaining transactions f r o m part of such`
  line `inter - connected transactions.`
  line `2 [ 24. Burden of proof. — In any proceeding relating to proceeds of crime under this Act, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of a person charged with the offence of money - laundering under section 3, the`
  line `Authority or Court shall, unless the contrary is proved, presume that such proceeds of crime are`
  line `involved in money - laundering; and`
  line `( b ) in the case of any other person the Authority or Court, may presume that such proce eds of`
  line `crime ar e involved in money - laundering.]`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPELLATE T RIBUNAL`
  line `3 [ 25. Appellate Tribunal. — The Appellate Tribunal constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12 of`
  line `the Smugglers and Foreign Exchange Manipulators (Forfeiture of Property) Act, 1976 (13 of 1976) shall`
  line `be the Appellate Tribunal for hearing appeals against the orders of the Adjudicating Authority and the`
  line `other authorities under this Act.]`
  line `26. Appeal to Appellate Tribunal. — ( 1 ) Save as otherwise provided in sub - section ( 3 ), the Direc tor`
  line `or any person aggrieved by an order made by the Adjudicating Authority under this Act, may prefer an`
  line `ap peal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `( 2 ) Any 4 [reporting entity] aggrieved by any order of the Director made under sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 13, may prefer an ap peal to the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `( 3 ) Every appeal preferred under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) shall be filed within a period of`
  line `forty - five days from the date on which a copy of the order made by the Adjudicating Authority or`
  line `Director is r eceived and it shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 1 8, for certain words and figure (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s.19, ibid., for section 24 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 232, for section 25 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 20, for “banking company, financial institution or intermediary” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving an opportunity of being heard, entertain an`
  line `appeal after the expiry of the said period of forty - five days if i t is satisfied that there was sufficient cause`
  line `for no t filing it within that period.`
  line `( 4 ) On receipt of an appeal under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ), the Appellate Tribunal may, after`
  line `giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard, pas s such orders thereon as it thinks fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or setting as ide the order appealed against.`
  line `( 5 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the appeal and`
  line `to the concerned Adjudicating Authority or th e Director, as the case may be.`
  line `( 6 ) The appeal filed before the Appellate Tribunal under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) shall be`
  line `dealt with by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal`
  line `finally within s ix months from the date of filin g of the appeal.`
  line `27. [ Compositio n s, etc., of Appellate Tribunal. ] Omitted by the Finance Act, 2016 ( 28 of 2016 ),`
  line `s. 232 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016 ).`
  line `28. [ Qualifications for appointment.] Omitted by s. 232, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `29. [ Term of office.] Omitted by the Prevention of Money - laundering ( Amendment ) Act, 2005`
  line `(20 of 2005), s. 4 ( w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005 ).`
  line `30. [ Conditions of service. ] Omitted by the Finance Act, 2016 ( 28 of 2016 ), s. 232 ( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016 ).`
  line `31. [ Vacancies. ] Omitted by s. 232, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `32. [ Resignation and removal. ] Omitted by s. 232, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `33. [ Member to act as Chairp erson in certain c ircumstances. ] Omitted by s. 232, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `3 4. [ Staff of Appellate Tribunal. ] Omitted by s. 232, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `35. Procedure an d powers of Appellate Tribunal. — ( 1 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall not be bound`
  line `by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the`
  line `principles of natural justice and, subject to the other P rovisions of this Act, the Appellate Tribunal shall`
  line `have powers to regulate its own procedure.`
  line `( 2 ) The Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the`
  line `same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matter s, namely: —`
  line `( a ) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any pe rson and examining him on oath;`
  line `( b ) requiring the discove ry and production of documents;`
  line `( c ) re ceiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( d ) subject to the pro visions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of`
  line `1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such reco rd or document from any`
  line office;
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for the examina tion of witnesses or documents;`
  line `( f ) review ing its decisions;`
  line `( g ) dismissing a representation for default or decid ing it ex parte;`
  line `( h ) setting aside any order of dismissal of any representation for default or any o rder passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line `( i ) any other matter, which may be, prescr ibed by the Central Government.`
  line `( 3 ) An order made by the Appellate Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal as a decree of civil court and, for this purpose, the Appellate Tribunal shall have a ll the powers`
  line `of a civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `( 4 ) Notwithst anding anything contained in sub - section ( 3 ), the Appellate Tribunal may transmit any`
  line `order made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order as if`
  line `it were a decree made by that court.`
  line `( 5 ) All proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within`
  line `the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes o f s ections 345 and 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line `36. Distribution of business amongst Benches. — Where any Benches are constituted, the`
  line `1 [ Chair man] may, from time to time, by notification, make provisions as to the distribution of the business`
  line `of the Appellate Tribunal amongst the Benches and also provid e for the matters which may be dealt with`
  line `by each Bench.`
  line `37. Power of 1 [ Chair man] to transfer cases. — On the application of any of the parties and after`
  line `notice to the parties, and after hearing such of them as he may desire to be heard, or on his own motion`
  line `without such notice, the 1 [Chairman] may transfer any c ase pending before one Bench, for disposal, t o`
  line `any other Bench.`
  line `38. Decision to be by majority. — If the Members of a Bench consisting of two Members differ in`
  line `opinion on any point, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the`
  line `1 [Chairman] who shal l either hear the point or point s himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or`
  line `points by 2 [third Member] of the Appellate Tribunal and such point or points shall be decided according`
  line `to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Appellate Tribunal who h ave heard the case,`
  line `including those who first heard it.`
  line `39. Right of appellan t to take assistance of authoris ed representative and of Government to`
  line `appoint prese nting officers. — ( 1 ) A person preferring an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under this Act`
  line `may either appear in person or take the assistance of an au thorised representative of his choice to present`
  line `his case before the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub - section, the expression “ authorised representative ” shall`
  line `have the same meaning as assigned to it under sub - sec t i on ( 2 ) of section 288 of the Inc ome - tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961).`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government or the Director may authorise one or more authorised representatives or`
  line `any of its officers to act as p resenting officers and every person so authorised may present the case with`
  line `respect to any appeal before the Appellate Tribun al.`
  line `40. Members, etc., to be public se rvants. — The 1 [Chairman], Members and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Appellate Tribunal, the Adjudicating Authority, Director and the officers subordinate to`
  line `him shall be deemed to be p ublic servants within the meanin g of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45`
  line `of 1860).`
  line `41. Civil court not to have jurisdiction. — No civil court shall have juris diction to entertain any suit`
  line `or proceeding in respect of any matter which the Director, an Adjudicating Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal is empowered by or und er this Act to dete rmine and no injunction shall be granted by any court`
  line `or other authority i n respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `42. Appeal to High Court. — Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court within sixty days from the date of communication of the`
  line `decision or order of the Appell ate Tribunal to him on any quest ion of law or fact arising out of such order:`
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause fr om filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further p eriod not`
  line `exceeding sixty days.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 232, for “Chairperson” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 11, for “one or more of th e other Members” (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, “ High Court ” means —`
  line `( i ) the High Court within the jurisdiction of w hich the aggrieved party ordina rily resides or carries`
  line `on business or personally works for gain; and`
  line `( ii ) where the Central Government is the aggrieved party, the High Court within the jurisdiction`
  line `of which the respondent, or in a case where there are more than one respondent, any of the`
  line `respondents, ordinarily resides or carries on business or personal ly works for gain.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `S PECIAL C OURTS`
  line `43. Special Courts. — ( 1 ) The Central Government, in consultation with the Chief Justice of the High`
  line `Court, shall, for trial of offence punishable under section 4, by notification, designate one or more Courts`
  line `of Session as Special Court or Special Courts or such area or areas or for such case or class or group of`
  line `cases as may be specified in the notification.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub - sect ion, “ High Court ” means the High Court of the State in which a`
  line `Sessions Court designated as Special Court was functioning immed iately before such designation.`
  line `( 2 ) While trying an offence under this Act, a Special Court shall also try an offence, other than an`
  line `offence referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), be charged at the same trial.`
  line `44. Offe nces triable by Special Courts. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Crimina l Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), —`
  line `1 [( a ) an offence punishable under section 4 and any scheduled offence connected to the offence`
  line `under that section shall be triable by the Special Court constituted for the area in which the offence`
  line `has been committed:`
  line `Provided that the Special Court, trying a scheduled offence before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `shall continue to try such scheduled offence; or];`
  line `( b ) a Special Court may, 2 *** upon a complaint made by an authority authorised in this behalf`
  line `under this Ac t take 3 [cognizance of offence under section 3, without the accused being committed to`
  line `it for trial];`
  line `4 [Provided that after conclusion of investigation, if no offence of money - laundering is made out`
  line `requiring filing of such complaint, the said authority shall submit a closure report before the Special`
  line `Court; or]`
  line `5 [( c ) if the court which has taken cognizance of the scheduled offence is other than the Special`
  line `Court which has taken cognizance of the complaint of the offence of money - laundering under`
  line `sub - cla use ( b), it shall, on an application by the authority authorised to file a complaint under this`
  line `Act, commit the case relating to the scheduled offence to the Special Court and the Special Court`
  line `shall, on receipt of such case proceed to deal with it from th e stage at which it is committed.`
  line `( d ) a Special Court while trying the scheduled offence or the offence of money - laundering shall`
  line `hold trial in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 ( 2 of 1974) as it`
  line `applies to a trial bef ore a Court of Session.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is clarified that, —`
  line `( i ) the jurisdiction of the Special Court while dealing with the offence under this Act, during`
  line `investigation, enquiry or trial under this Act, shall not be dependent upon any orders passed in`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 21, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. The words “ upon perusal of police report of the facts which constitute an offence under this Act or” omitted by Act`
  line `20 of 2005, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 21, for “cognizance of the offence for which the accused is committed to it for trial”`
  line `(w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. I ns. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 199 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 21 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `respect of the scheduled offence, and the trial of both sets of o ffences by the same court shall not`
  line `be construed as joint trial;`
  line `( ii ) the complaint shall be deemed to include any subsequent complaint in respect of further`
  line `investigation that may be conducted to bring any further evidence, oral or documentary, against`
  line `an y accused person involved in respect of the offence, for which complaint has already been`
  line `filed, whether named in the original complaint or not. ]`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to affect the special powers of the High Court`
  line `regarding bail under sec t i on 439 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the High Court`
  line `may exercise such powers including the power unde r clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of that section as if the`
  line `reference to “ Magistrate ” in that section includes als o a reference to a “ Special Court ” designated under`
  line `section 43.`
  line `45. Offences to be cognizable and non - bailable. — ( 1 ) 1 [Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no person accused of an offence 2 [under this Act] shall be`
  line `released on bail or on his own bond unless — ]`
  line `( i ) the Pub lic Prosecutor has been given a opportunity to oppose the ap plication for such`
  line `release; and`
  line `( ii ) where the Public Prosecutor opposes the application, the court is satisfied that there are`
  line `re asonable grounds for believing that he is not guilty of such offence and that he is not likely to`
  line `co mmit any offence while on bail:`
  line `Provided that a person, who, is under the age of sixteen years, or is a woman or is sick or infirm, 3 [or`
  line `is accused either on his own or along with other co - accused of money - laundering a sum of less than one`
  line `crore rupees] may be released on bail, i f the Special Court so directs:`
  line `Provided further that the Special Court shall not take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `s ection 4 except upon a complaint in writing made by —`
  line `( i ) the Director; or`
  line `( ii ) any officer of the Central Government or a State Government authorised in writing in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government by a general or special order made in this behalf by t hat`
  line Government.
  line `4 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), or`
  line `any other provision of this Act, no police officer shall investigate into an offence under this Act unless`
  line `specifically authorised, by the Cen tral Government by a general or special order, and, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed.]`
  line `( 2 ) The limitation on granting of bail specified in 5 *** sub - section ( 1 ) is in addition to the limitations`
  line `under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or any other law for the time being in force on`
  line `granting of bail.`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is clarified that the expression “ Offences to be`
  line `cognizable and non - bailable ” shall mean and shall be deemed to have always meant that a ll offences`
  line `under this Act shall be cognizable offences and non - bailable offences notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), and accordingly the officers`
  line `authorised under this Act are empowered t o arrest an accused without warrant, subject to the fulfillment`
  line `of conditions under section 19 and subject to the conditions enshrined under this section.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2005, s. 7, for certain words, figures, brackets and letters (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208, for “ punishable for a term of imprisonment of more than three years under Part A of the`
  line `Schedule ” (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 208, ibid., (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2005, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005).`
  line `5. The words, brackets and letter “clause ( b ) of” omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005).`
  line `6. The Explanation i ns. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 200 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-26
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Page 26`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `46. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to pr oceedings before Special Court. — ( 1 )`
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974) (including the provisions as to bails or bonds), shall apply to the proceedings before a Special`
  line `Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Spec ial Court shall be deemed to be a Court of`
  line `Session and the persons conducting the prosecution before the Special Court, sh all be deemed to be a`
  line `Public Prosecutor:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may also appoint for any case or class or group of cas es a`
  line `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  line `( 2 ) A person shall not be qualified to be appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor under this section unless he has been in practice as an advocate for not less than seven years,`
  line `under the Union or a Sta te, requ iring special knowledge of law.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person appointed as a Public Prosecutor or a Special Public Prosecutor under this section`
  line `shall be deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause ( u ) of section 2 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Proc edure, 1973 (2 of 1974) and the p rovisions of that Code shall have effect accordingly.`
  line `47. Appeal and revision. — The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the powers`
  line `conferred by Chapter XXIX or Chapter XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.`
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `A UTHORITIES`
  line `4 8. Authorities under Act. — There shall be the following classes of authorities for the purposes of`
  line `this Act, namely: —`
  line `( a ) Director or Additional Director or Joint Director,`
  line `( b ) Deputy Director,`
  line `( c ) Assistant Director, and`
  line `( d ) such other class of officers as may be appointed for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `49. Appointment and powers of authorities and other officers. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may`
  line `appoint such persons as it thinks fit to be authoritie s for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to th e provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may authorise the`
  line `Director or an Additional Director or a Joint Director or a Deputy Director or an Assistant Director`
  line `appointed under that sub - section to appoint other aut horities below the rank of a n Assistant Director.`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to such conditions and limitations as the Central Government may impose, an authority`
  line `may exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed on it under this Act.`
  line `50. Powers of authorities regarding summons, production of docum ents and to give evidence,`
  line `etc. — ( 1 ) The Director shall, for the purposes of section 13, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908 ) while trying a suit in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a 1 [reporting entity] and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compel ling the production of records;`
  line `( d ) re ceiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for examination of witness es and documents; and`
  line `( f ) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 22, for “banking company or a financial institution or a company,” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
