  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `( 2 ) The Director, Additional Director, Joint Director, Deputy Director or Assistant Director shall have`
  line `power to summon any person whose attendance he considers necessary whether to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any records during the course of any investi g atio n or proceeding under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) All the persons so summoned shall be bound to attend in person or through authorised agents, as`
  line `su ch officer may direct, and shall be bound to state the truth upon any subject respecting which they are`
  line `examined or make statements, and produce such documents as may be required.`
  line `( 4 ) Every proceeding under sub - sections ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding`
  line `within the meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `( 5 ) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the Central Government, any officer referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) may impound and retain in his c ustody for such period, as he thinks fit, any records`
  line `produced before him in any proceedings under this Act:`
  line `Provided that an Assistant Director or a Deputy Director shall not —`
  line `( a ) impound any records without recordi ng his reasons for so doing; or`
  line `( b ) reta in in his custody any such records for a period exceeding three months, without obtaining`
  line `the previous approval of the 1 [Joint Director ].`
  line `5 1. Jurisdiction of authorities. — ( 1 ) The authorities shall exercise all or any of the powers and`
  line `perform all or any of the functions conferred on, or, assigned, as the case may be, to such authorities by or`
  line `under this Act or the rules framed thereunder i n accordance with such directions as the Central`
  line `Government may issue for the exercise of powers and performance of the functions by all or any of the`
  line authorities.
  line `( 2 ) In issuing the directions or orders referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may have`
  line `regard to any one or more of t he following criteria, namely: —`
  line `( a ) territorial area;`
  line `( b ) classes of persons;`
  line `( c ) classes of cases; and`
  line `( d ) any other criterion specified by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line `52. Power of Central Government to is sue directions, etc. — The Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, issue such orders, instructions and directions to the authorities as it may deem fit for the`
  line `proper administration of this Act and such authorities an d all other persons employed in execution of this`
  line `Act shall observe and follow such orders, instructions and directions of the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or direc tions shall be issued so as to —`
  line `( a ) require any authority to decide a particular case in a parti cular manner; or`
  line `( b ) interfere with the discretion of the Adjudicating Authority in exercise of his functions.`
  line `53. E mpowerment of certain officers. — The Central Government may, by a special or general order,`
  line `empower an officer not below the rank of Director of the Central Gove rnment or of a State Government`
  line `to act as an authority under this Act:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may empower an officer below the rank of Director if the`
  line `officer of the rank of the Director or above are not available in a particular area.`
  line `54. Ce rtain offi cers to assist in inquiry, etc. — The following 2 [ officers and others] are hereby`
  line `empowered and required to assist the authorities in the en forcement of this Act, namely: —`
  line `( a ) officers of the Customs and Central Excise Departments;`
  line `( b ) officers appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5 of the Narcotic Drugs and`
  line `Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line `( c ) income - tax authorities under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 117 of the Inco me - tax Act, 1961 (43 of`
  line `1961);`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208, for “Director” (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 23 for “officers” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
