obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `1 [ ( d ) members of the recognised stock exchange referred to in clause ( f ) of section 2 and the`
  line `officers of the stock exchanges recognised under section 4 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation)`
  line `Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); ]`
  line `( e ) officers of the Reserve Bank of India constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line `( f ) officers of Police;`
  line `( g ) officers of enforcement appointed under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 36 of the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Man agement Act, 1999 (40 of 1999);`
  line `( h ) officers of the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board o f India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);`
  line `2 [ (ha) officers of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority established under`
  line `section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999);`
  line `(hb) officers of the Forward Markets Commission established under section 3 of the Forward`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952);`
  line `(hc ) officers and members of the recognised association recognised under section 6 of the`
  line `Forward Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1952 (74 of 1952);`
  line `(hd) officers of the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority;`
  line `(he) officers of the Department of Posts in the Government of India;`
  line `(hf) Registrars or Sub - Registrars appointed by the State Governments under section 6 of the`
  line `Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908);`
  line `(hg) registering authority empowered to register motor vehicles under Chapter IV of the Motor`
  line `Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988);`
  line `(hh) officers and members of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949);`
  line `(hi) officers and members of the Institute of Cost and Works Accountants of I ndia constituted`
  line `under section 3 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959);`
  line `(hj) officers and members of the Institute of Company Secretaries of India constituted under`
  line `section 3 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980);]`
  line `( i ) officers of any other body corporate constituted or established unde r a Central Act or a State`
  line Act;
  line `( j ) such other officers of the Central Government, State Government, local authorities or`
  line `3 [reporting entities] as the Central Government may, by notificati on, specify, in this behalf.`
  line `CHAPTER IX`
  line `R ECIPROCAL A RRANGEMENT FOR A SSISTANCE IN C ERTAIN M ATTERS AND P ROCEDURE FOR`
  line `A TTACHMENT AND C ONFISCATION OF P ROPERTY`
  line `55. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context other wise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ contracting State ” means any country or place outside India in respect of which arrangements`
  line `have been made by the Central Government with the Government of such country through a treaty or`
  line otherwise;
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 23, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 23, ibid. (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for “banking companies” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
