obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line `( b ) “ identifying ” includes establishment of a proof that the property was derived from, or used in`
  line `the commission of an offence under section 3;`
  line `( c ) “ tracing ” means determining the nature, source, disposition, movement, title or ownership of`
  line property.
  line `56. Ag reements with foreign countries. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may enter i nto an agreement`
  line `with the Government of any country outside India for —`
  line `( a ) enforc ing the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( b ) exchange of information for the prevention of any offence under this Act or under the`
  line `corresponding law in force in that country or investigation of cases relating to any offence under this`
  line Act,
  line `and may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make suc h provisions as may be necessary for`
  line `implementing the agreement.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that the application of`
  line `this Chapter in relation to a contracting State with which reciprocal arrangements have been made, shall`
  line `be subject to such conditions, exceptions or q ualifications as are specified in the said notification.`
  line `57. Letter of request to a cont racting State in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or the Code of Crimin al Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) if, in the course of an`
  line `investigation into an offence or other proceedings under this Ac t, an application is made to a Special`
  line `Court by the Investigating Officer or any officer superior in rank to the Investigating Officer th at any`
  line `evidence is required in connection with investigation into an offence or proceedings under this Act and he`
  line `is o f the opinion that such evidence may be available in any place in a contracting State, and the Special`
  line `Court, on being satisfied that such evidence is required in connection with the investigation into an`
  line `offence or proceedings under this Act, may issue a letter of request to a court or an authority in the`
  line `contracting State competen t to deal with such request to —`
  line `( i ) examine facts and circum stances of the case,`
  line `( ii ) take such steps as the Special Court may specify in such letter of request, and`
  line `( iii ) forward all the evidence so taken or collected to the Special Court issuing such letter of`
  line request.
  line `( 2 ) The letter of request shall be transmit ted in such manner as the Central Governm ent may specify`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) Every statement recorded or document or thing received under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to`
  line `be the evidence collected during the course of investigation.`
  line `58. Assistance to a cont racting State in certain cases. — Where a letter of request is received by the`
  line `Central Government from a court or authority in a contracting State requesting for investigation into an`
  line `offence or procee dings under this Act and forward ing to such court or authority any evidence connected`
  line `therewith, the Central Government may forward such letter of request to the Special Court or to any`
  line `authority under the Act as it thinks fit for execution of such reques t in accordance with the provisi ons of`
  line `this Act or, as the case may be, any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `1 [ 58A. Special Court to release the property. — Where on closure of the criminal case or conclusion`
  line `of a trial in a criminal court outside India under the corresponding law of any other country, such court`
  line `finds that the offence of money - laundering has not taken place or the property in India is not involved in`
  line `money - laundering, the Special Court may, on an application moved by the concerned person or the`
  line `Director, after notice to the other party, order release of such property to the person entitled to receive it.`
  line `58B. Letter of request of a contracting State or authority for confiscation or release the`
  line `property. — Where the trial under the corresponding law of any other country cannot be conducted by`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 24 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
