obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `reason of the death of the accused or the accused being declared a proclaimed offender or for any other`
  line `reason or having commenced but could not be concluded, the Centr al Government shall, on receipt of a`
  line `letter of request from a court or authority in a contracting State requesting for confiscation or release of`
  line `property, as the case may be, forward the same to the Director to move an application before the Special`
  line `Court and upon such application the Special Court shall pass appropriate orders regarding confiscation or`
  line `release of such property involved in the offence of money - laundering.]`
  line `59. Reciprocal arrangements for processes and assistance f or transfer of accused per sons. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where a Special Court, in relation to an offence punishable under section 4, desires that —`
  line `( a ) a s ummons to an accused person, or`
  line `( b ) a warrant for the arrest of an accused person, or`
  line `( c ) a summons to any person requiring him to attend and produc e a document or o ther thing or to`
  line `produce it, or`
  line `( d ) a search warrant,`
  line `issued by it shall be served or executed at any place in any contracting State, it shall send such summons`
  line `or warrant in duplicate in such form, to such Court, Judge or Magistrate thro ugh such authorities, as the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification, s pecify in this behalf and that Court, Judge or Magistrate, as`
  line `the case may be, shall cause the same to be executed.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a Special Court, in relation to an offence punishable under section 4 has rec eived for`
  line `service or execution —`
  line `( a ) a s ummons to an accused person, or`
  line `( b ) a warrant for the arrest of an accused person, or`
  line `( c ) a summons to any person requiring him to attend and produce a document or ot her thing, or to`
  line `produce it, or`
  line `( d ) a search warrant,`
  line `issued by a Court, Judge or Magistrate in a contracting State, it shall, cause the same to be served or`
  line `executed as if it were a summons or warrant received by it from another Court in the said territories for`
  line `service or ex ecution within its local jurisdiction; and where —`
  line `( i ) a warrant of arrest has been executed, the person arrested shall be dealt with in accordance`
  line `with the proced ure specified under section 19;`
  line `( ii ) a search warrant has been executed, the things found in this sear ch shall, so far as possible, be`
  line `dealt with in accordance with the procedure spec ified under sections 17 and 18:`
  line `Provided that in a case where a summon or search warrant received from a contracting State has been`
  line `executed, the documents or other things pro duced or things found in the search shall be forwarded to the`
  line `Court issuing the summons or search - warrant throug h such authority as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notifi cation, specify in this behalf.`
  line `( 3 ) Where a person transferred to a contracting State p ursuant to sub - section ( 2 ) is a prisoner in India,`
  line `the Special Court or the Central Government may impose such conditions as that Court or Government`
  line `deems fit.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the person transferred to India pursuant to sub - section ( 1 ) is a prisoner in a contr acting`
  line `State, the Special Court in India shall ensure that the conditions subject to which the prisoner is`
  line `transferred to India a re complied with and such prisoner shall be kept in such custody subject to such`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may direct in writing.`
