  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  sourcePage 31
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line 31
  line `60. Attachment, seizure and confiscation, etc., of property i n a contracting State or India. — ( 1 )`
  line `Where the Director has made an order for attachment of any 1 [property under section 5 or for freezing`
  line `under sub - section ( 1A ) of section 17 or where an Adjudicating Authority has made an order relating to a`
  line `property under section 8 or where a Special Court has made an order of confiscation relating to a prop erty`
  line `under sub - section ( 5 ) or sub - section ( 6 ) of section 8] and such property is suspected to be in a contracting`
  line `State, the Special Court, on an application by the Director or the Administrator appointed under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 10, as the case may b e, may issue a letter of request to a court or an authority in`
  line `the contracting Sta te for execution of such order.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a letter of request is received by the Central Government from a court or an authority in a`
  line `contracting State requesting 2 [ att achment, seizure, freezing or confiscation ] of the property in India,`
  line `derived or obtained, directly or indire ctly, by any person from the com mission of an offence under 3 [a`
  line `corresponding law] committed in that contracting State, the Central Government may forward such letter`
  line `of request to the Director, as it thinks fit, for execution in accordance w ith the provisions of this Act.`
  line `4 [ ( 2A ) Where on closure of the criminal case or conclusion of trial in a criminal court outside India`
  line `under the corresponding law of any other country, such court finds that the offence of money - laundering`
  line `under the corresponding law of that country has been committed, the 5 [Special Court] shall, on receipt of`
  line `an application from the Director for execution of confiscation under sub - section ( 2 ), order, after giving`
  line `notice to the affected persons, that such property involved in money - laundering or which has been used`
  line `for commission of the off ence of money - laundering stand confisc ated to the Central Government.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Director shall, on receipt of a letter of request under section 58 or section 59, direct any`
  line `authority under this Act to take all steps necessary for tracing and identifying suc h property.`
  line `( 4 ) The steps referred to in sub - section ( 3 ) may include any inquiry, investigation or survey in respect`
  line `of any person, place, property, assets, documents, books of account in any bank or public financial`
  line `institutions or any other relevant matt ers.`
  line `( 5 ) Any inquiry, investigation or survey referred to in sub - section ( 4 ) shall be carried out by an`
  line `authority mentioned in sub - section ( 3 ) in accordance with such directions issued in accordance w ith the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) The provisions of th is Act relating to attachment, adjudication, confiscation and vesting of`
  line `property in the Central Government contained in Chapter III and survey, searches and seizures contained`
  line `in Chapter V shall apply to the property in respect of which letter of request is received from a court or`
  line `contracting State for attachment or confiscation of property.`
  line `6 [( 7 ) When any property in India is confiscated as a result of execution of a request from a contracting`
  line `State in accordance with the provisions of this Act, the Cent ral Government may either return such`
  line `property to the requesting State or compensate that State by disposal of such property on mutually agreed`
  line `terms that would take into account deduction for reasonable expenses incurred in investigation,`
  line `prosecution or j udicial proceedings leading to the return or disposal of confiscated property.]`
  line `61. Procedure i n respect of letter of request. — Every letter of request, summons or warrant,`
  line `received by the Central Government from, and every letter of request, summons or warrant, to be`
  line `transmitted to a contracting State under this Chapter shall be transmitted to a contracting State or, as the`
  line `case m ay be, sent to the concerned Court in India and in such form and in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 25, for certain words and figures (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for “attachment or confiscation” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 25, ibid., for “section 3” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 150, for “Adjudicating Authority” (w.e.f. 14 - 5 - 2015).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2009, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2009).`
