  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  sourcePage 32
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line 32
  line `CHAPTER X`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `62. P unishment for vexatious search. — Any authority or officer exercising powers under this Act or`
  line `any rules made thereunder, who, without reaso ns recorded in writing, —`
  line `( a ) searches or causes to be sea rched any building or place; or`
  line `( b ) detains or searches or arrests any person,`
  line `shall for every such offence be liable on conviction for imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years or fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or both.`
  line `63. Punishment for false information or fa ilure to give information, etc. — ( I ) Any person wilfully`
  line `and maliciously giving false information and so causing an arrest or a search to be made under this Act`
  line `shall on conviction be liable for imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or with fine`
  line `which may extend to fifty thousand rupees or both.`
  line `( 2 ) If any person, —`
  line `( a ) being legally bou nd to state the truth of any matter relating to an offence under section 3,`
  line `refuses to answer any question put to him by an authority in the exercise of its powers under this`
  line `Act; or`
  line `( b ) refuses to sign any statement made by him in the course of any proceedings under this Act,`
  line `which an authority may legally require to sig n; or`
  line `( c ) to whom a summon is issued under section 50 either to attend to give evidence or produce`
  line `books of account or other documents at a certain place and time, omits to atten d or produce books of`
  line `account or documents at the place or time,`
  line `he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees fo r each such default or failure.`
  line `( 3 ) No order under this section shall be passed by an authority referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) unless the`
  line `person on whom the penalty is proposed to be imposed is given an opportunity of being heard in the`
  line `matter by such authority.`
  line `1 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in claus e ( c ) of sub - section ( 2 ), a person who intentionally`
  line `disobeys any direction issued under section 50 shall also be liable to be proceeded against under`
  line `section 174 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
  line `64. Cognizance of offences. — ( 1 ) No court shal l take cognizance of any offence under section 62 or`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 63 except with the previous sanc tion of the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall, by an order, either give sanction or refuse to give sanction within`
  line `ninety day s of the receipt of the request in this behalf.`
  line `65. Code of Criminal Procedure, 197 3 to apply. — The provisions of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply, in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Act, to arrest, search and seizure, attachment, confiscation investigation, prosecution and all other`
  line `proceedings under this Act.`
  line `66. Disclosure of information. — 2 [ ( 1 ) ] The Director or any other authority specified by him by a`
  line `general or special order in this behal f may furni sh or cause to be furnished to —`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s.26 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Section 66 numbered as sub - section ( 1 ) by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-33
