  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  sourcePage 33
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line 33
  line `( i ) any officer, authority or body performing any functions under any law relating to imposition of`
  line `any tax, duty or cess or to dealings in foreign exchange, or prevention of illicit traffic in the narcotic`
  line `drugs and psycho tropic substances under the Narc otic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985`
  line `(61 o f 1985); or`
  line `( ii ) such other officer, authority or body performing fu nctions under any other law as the Central`
  line `Government may, if in its opinion it is necessary so to do in the public interest, specify, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, in this beha lf, any inf ormation received or obtained by such`
  line `Director or any oth er authority, specified by him in the performance of their functions under this Act,`
  line `as may, in the opinion of the Director or the other authority, so specified by him, be necessary for the`
  line `purpose of the officer, authority or body specified in clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) to perform his or its`
  line `functions under that law.`
  line `1 [( 2 ) If the Director or other authority specified under sub - section ( 1 ) is of the opinion, on the basis of`
  line `information or material in his possession, that the provisions of any other law for t he time being in force`
  line `are contravened, then the Director or such other author ity shall share the information with the concerned`
  line `agency for necessary action.]`
  line `67. Bar of suits in civil courts. — No suit shall be brought in any civil court to set aside or mod ify`
  line `any proceeding taken or order made under this Act and no prosecution, suit or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Gover nment or any officer of the Government for anything done or intended to be done in`
  line `good faith under this Act.`
  line `68. Notice, etc., no t to be invalid on certain g rounds. — No notice, summons, order, document or`
  line `other proceeding, furnished or made or issued or taken or purported to have been furnished or made or`
  line `issued or taken in pursuance of any of the provisions of his Act shall be invalid, or shall be deemed to be`
  line `invalid merely by reason of any mistake, defect or omission in such notice, summons, order, document or`
  line `other proceeding if such notice, summons, order, document or other p roceeding is in substance and effect`
  line `in conformity with or according to the intent and purpose of this Act.`
  line `2 [ 69. Recovery of fine or penalty. — Where any fine or penalty imposed on any person under`
  line `section 13 or section 63 is not paid within six months from the day of imposition of fine or p enalty, the`
  line `Director or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf may proceed to recover the amount from the`
  line `said person in the same manner as prescribed in Schedule II of the Income - tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) for`
  line `the recovery of arrears and he or any officer authorised by him in this behalf shall have all the powers of`
  line `the Tax Recovery Officer mentioned in the said Schedule for the said purpose.]`
  line `70. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where a person committing a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder is a company, every person who,`
  line `at the time the contravention was committed, was in charge of and was responsible to the company, for`
  line `the conduct of the business of the company as well as the comp any, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `contravention and shall be liable to be proceeded ag ainst and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to punishment`
  line `if he proves that the contrav ention took place without his knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence`
  line `to pre vent such contravention.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or of any rule, direction or order made thereunder has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the cont ravention has taken plac e with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of any comp any,`
  line `such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be gu ilty of the contraventi on`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded ag ainst and punished accordingly.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 208 (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2018).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 27, for section 69 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-34
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Page 34`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  sourcePage 34
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line 34
  line `Explanation 1 [ 1 ]. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “ company ” means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line `( ii ) “ director ”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that a company may be prosecuted,`
  line `notwithstanding whether the prosecution or conviction of any legal juridical person shall be contingent on`
  line `the prosecution or conviction of any individual.]`
  line `71. Act to have overriding effect. — The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `72. Continuation of proceedings in th e event of death or insolvency. — ( 1 ) Where —`
  line `( a ) any property of a person s has been attached under section 8 and no appeal against the order`
  line `attaching such property has been preferred; or`
  line `( b ) any appeal has been preferred to the Appellat e Tribunal, and —`
  line `( i ) in a case referred to in clause ( a ), such person d ies or is adjudicated an insolvent before`
  line `preferring an appea l to the Appellate Tribunal; or`
  line `( ii ) in a case referred to in clause ( b ), such person dies or is adjudicated an insolvent dur ing`
  line `the pendency of the appeal,`
  line `then, it shall be lawful for the legal representatives of such person or the official assignee or the official`
  line `receiver, as the case may be, to prefer an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal or as the case may be, to`
  line `continue the appeal before the Appellate T ribunal, in place of such person and th e provisions of`
  line `section 26 shall, so far as may be, apply, or con tinue to apply, to such appeal.`
  line `( 2 ) Where —`
  line `( a ) after passing of a decision or order by the Appellate Tribunal, no appeal has been preferred to`
  line `the High court under section 42; or`
  line `( b ) any such appeal has been pref erred to the High Court, —`
  line `then —`
  line `( i ) in a case referred to in clause ( a ), the person entitled to file the appeal dies or is adjudicated an`
  line `insolvent before preferring an appeal to the High Court, or`
  line `( ii ) in a case referred t o in clause ( b ), the person who had filed the appeal dies or is adjudicated an`
  line `insolvent during the pendency of the appeal before the High Court,`
  line `then, it shall be lawful for the legal representatives of such person, or the official assignee or the offici al`
  line `receiver, as the case may be, to prefer an appeal to the High Court or to continue the appeal before the`
  line `High Court in place of such person an d the provision s of section 42 shall, so far as may be, apply, or`
  line `con tinue to apply, to such appeal.`
  line `( 3 ) The powers of the official assignee or the official receiver under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 )`
  line `shall be exercised by him subject to the provisions of the Presidency - towns Insolvency Act, 1909`
  line `(3 of 1909) or the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 ( 5 of 1920), as the case may be.`
  line `3 [ 72A. Inter - ministerial Co - ordination Committee. — The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, constitute an Inter - ministerial Co - ordination Committee for inter - departmenta l and inter -`
  line `agency co - ordination for t he following purposes, namely: —`
  line `1. Explanation shall be numbered as Explanatio n 1 by Act 2 of 2013, s. 28, (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013)`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 28, ibid. (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 201 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
