  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `( a ) operational co - operation between the Government, law enforcement agencies, the Financial`
  line `Intelligence Unit, India and the regulators or supervisors;`
  line `( b ) policy co - operation and co - or dination across all relevant or competent authorities;`
  line `( c ) such consultation among the concerned authorities, the financial sector and other sectors, as`
  line `are appropriate, and are related to anti money - laundering or countering the financing of terrorism`
  line `laws, regulations and guidelines;`
  line `( d ) development and implementing policies on anti money - laundering or countering the financing`
  line `of terrorism; and`
  line `( e ) any other matter as the Central Government may, by notification, specify in this behalf.]`
  line `73. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matter s, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the form in which records referred to in this Act may be maintained;`
  line `1 [ ( aa ) the manner of provisional attachment of property under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 5;]`
  line `( b ) the manner in which the order and the material referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 5 to be`
  line maintained;
  line `( c ) matters in respect of experience of Members unde r sub - section ( 3 ) of section 6;`
  line `( d ) the salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of servi ce of Members`
  line `of the Adjudicating Authority under sub - s ection ( 9 ) of section 6;`
  line `( e ) the salaries and allowances payable to and other terms and conditions of service of the officers`
  line `and employees of the Adjudicating Authority unde r sub - section ( 3 ) of sectio n 7;`
  line `1 [ ( ee ) the manner of seizing or taking possession of property attached under section 5 or frozen`
  line `under sub - section ( 1A ) of section 17 or under sub - section ( 4) of section 8;]`
  line `( f ) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which the properties confiscated may be`
  line `received and managed under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 10;`
  line `( g ) the additional matters in respect of which the Adjudicating Authority may exercise the powers`
  line `of a civil court under clause ( f ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 11;`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( i ) 3 [the nature and value of transactions and the time within which ] the information of`
  line `transactions under clause ( b ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of sectio n 12 shall be furnished;`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [( jja ) the manner and the conditions in which authentication of the identity of clients shall be`
  line `verified by the reporting entities under clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12AA;`
  line `( jjb ) the manner of identifying the ownership and financial position of the clien t under clause ( b )`
  line `of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 12AA;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 29 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Clause ( h ) omitted by s. 29, ibid. (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 29, ibid., for “the time within which” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Clause s ( j ) and ( jj ) omitted by Act 14 of 2019, s. 2 9 (w.e.f. 25 - 07 - 2019).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 202 (w.e.f. 1 - 8 - 2019).`
