obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line 36
  line `( jjc ) additional steps to record the purpose behind conducting the specified transaction and the`
  line `intended nature of the relationship between the transaction parties under clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 12AA;`
  line `( jjd ) manner of increasing the future monitoring under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 12AA.]`
  line `( jjj ) the period of interval in which the reports are sent by the reporting entities or any of its`
  line `employees under clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of se ction 13;]`
  line `( k ) the procedure and the manner of maintaining and furnishing information under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 1 2 as required under section 15;`
  line `( l ) the manner in which the reasons and the material referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 16`
  line `shall be maintained;`
  line `( m ) the rules relating to search and seizure under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 17;`
  line `( n ) the manner in which the reasons and the material referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 17`
  line `shall be maintained;`
  line `( o ) the manner in which the reasons and the material referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 18`
  line `shal l be maintained;`
  line `( p ) the manner in which the order and the material referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 19`
  line `shall be maintained;`
  line `1 [ (pp ) the manner in which the forwarding o f the order for retention or continuation of freezing of`
  line `the property and the period of keeping such order and material under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 20;]`
  line `( q ) the manner in which records authenticated outside India may be received under`
  line `sub - section ( 2 ) of section 22;`
  line `( r ) the form of appeal and the fee for filing such appeal, under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 26;`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( u ) the additional matters in respect of which the Appellate Tribunal may exercise the powers of a`
  line `civil court under clause ( i ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 35;`
  line `3 [( ua ) conditions subject to which a police officer may be authorised to investigate into an`
  line `offence under sub - section ( 1A ) of section 45;]`
  line `( v ) the additional matters in respect of which the authorities may exercise pow ers of a civil court`
  line `under clause ( f ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 50;`
  line `( w ) the rules relating to impounding and custody of records under sub - section ( 5 ) of section 50;`
  line `( x ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `74. Rule s to be laid before Parliament. — Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or i n two or more suc cessive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be m ade, the`
  line `rule shal l thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 2013, s. 29 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Clauses ( s ) and ( t ) o mitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 232 (w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2005, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 2005).`
