  line `PARAGRAPH 5`
  line `O FFENCES UNDER THE A RMS A CT, 1959`
  line `(54 OF 1959)`
  line `Section Description of offence`
  line `25 To manufacture, sell, transfer, convert, repair or test or prove or expose or offer for sale or`
  line `transfer or have in his possession for sale, transfer, conversion, repair, test or proof, any arms`
  line `or ammunition in contravention of section 5 of the Arms Act, 1959.`
  line `To acqui re, have in possession or carry any prohibited arms or prohibited ammunition in`
  line `contravention of section 7 of the Arms Act, 1959.`
  line `Contravention of section 24A of the Arms Act, 1959 relating to prohibition as to possession of`
  line `notified arms in disturbed areas, etc.`
  line `Contravention of section 24B of the Arms Act, 1959 relating to prohibition as to carrying of`
  line `notified arms in or through public places in disturbed areas.`
  line `Other o ffences specified in section 25.`
  line `26 To do any act in contravention of any provisions of section 3, 4, 10 or section 12 of`
  line `the Arms Act, 1959 in such manner as specified in sub - section ( 1 ) of section 26 of the said`
  line Act.
  line `To do any act in contravention of any p rovi sions of section 5, 6, 7 or section 11 of`
  line `the Arms Act, 1959 in such manner as specified in sub - section ( 2 ) of section 26 of the said`
  line Act.
  line `Other o ffences specified in section 26.`
  line `27 Use of arms or ammunitions in contravention of section 5 or use of any arms or ammunition in`
  line `contravention of section 7 of the Arms Act, 1959.`
  line `28 Use and possession of fire arms or imitation fire arms in certain cases.`
  line `29 Knowingly purchasing arms from unlicensed person or for delivering arms, etc., to person not`
  line `entitled to possess the same.`
  line `30 Contravention of any condition of a licence or any provisions of the Arms Act, 1959 or any`
  line `rule made thereunder.`
  line `PARAGRAPH 6`
